distribution with degrees of freedom
@math{n} and @math{m}, respectively.  Then
m4_displaymath(
<<<F = {S_1/n \over S_2/m}>>>,
<<<@math{F = (S_1/n)/(S_2/m)}>>>) has an @math{F} distribution with @math{n} and @math{m} degrees of
